Source:  Collins Guide
Author:  AYLING
Vol / Page:  196
Edition:  1984
Quote:  <i>SEA PERCH (Jock Stewart, Matua-whapuku)</i> Helicolenus <i>percoides (Helicolenus papilosus)</i> ... Sea perch are similar in shape and appearance to the scorpion fish but have smoother heads ... It is a deep water species ... more common to the south of Cook Strait. ... In deep southern waters sea perch are a fairly uniform pale yellow-brown with a white belly and further work may show this to be a separate species.
